##Zhong Nanshan: BE ON HIGH ALERT FOR IMPORTED CASES, the first wave of the epidemic is highly contagious!

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

At 0-24 on the 17th, there were no new suspected cases in mainland China for the first time, and 13 new confirmed cases were reported. Among them, 12 new cases were imported from abroad.

Domestic epidemic situation continues to be good, the importation of overseas cases has become the focus of many people's attention, but also caused some controversy. Why is the importation of foreign viruses of concern? What is the import situation outside Beijing Capital International Airport? On the 18th, some of the announcements in Beijing and Guangzhou may offer some explanation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photograph: Guangzhou Evening News

Zhong Nanshan: BE ON HIGH ALERT FOR IMPORTED cases

Guangzhou held a press briefing on the prevention and control of the epidemic on the 18th. Zhong Nanshan, an academician at the Chinese Academy of Engineering, says that because China has adopted the world's strongest intervention, cases are now fewer and fewer. But most countries are now in the first wave of the epidemic, and patients are characterized by high levels of infectivity and are infectious when they are asymptomatic. He urged all places to be on high alert for imported cases and to do nucleic acid testing.

He added that infectious diseases know no borders and no country can escape them. New Pneumonia can not go away without strong intervention, and all countries need to act.

Beijing and Beijing Capital International Airport face unprecedented imported risks

At a press conference held by the Government of Beijing on the 18th, Zheng Nan, deputy director of the Beijing Capital International Airport Public Security Bureau in Beijing, said there had been a significant increase in inbound tourists to Beijing Capital International Airport recently, this is closely related to the recent epidemic situation in some foreign countries and regions, and Beijing Capital International Airport ports are facing unprecedented import risks.

Previously, the city of Beijing has stipulated that from March 16,00 hours, all foreign visitors to Beijing, should be transferred to a centralized observation point for 14 days of isolation observation. Under special circumstances, after strict assessment, home observation can be carried out. During the period of centralized isolation observation, isolation personnel costs need to be covered by themselves.

Beijing, China Suspends Foreign Students from China

Beijing Center for Disease Control and Prevention Deputy Director Pang Xinghuo said on the 18th, if it is not very necessary, should suspend travel arrangements to return or to countries or regions affected by the epidemic, to reduce the risk of infection caused by long-distance travel. When there is a need to return, should assess their health, suffering from acute illness or chronic diseases must avoid travel.

She also said that the risk of cases was higher among passengers arriving via flights EY888, SU204, EK306 and CA846, based on the number of flights imported into Beijing.

Beijing will crack down on overseas purchases made on behalf of Chinese consumers, regardless of epidemic prevention and control requirements

Beijing Capital International Airport Public Security Bureau said on the 18th, do not listen to dissuade, insist to South Korea and other places to buy on behalf of, after entering the country and do not comply with quarantine regulations, will resolutely crack down on the treatment in accordance with the law, effectively prevent the importation of foreign epidemic.

The Beijing Municipal Public Security Bureau had previously detained 36 people who frequently traveled to South Korea to work in Daigou and transferred them to a designated place for quarantine observation, in addition, two persons who did not comply with the relevant regulations on segregation issued by the government and who instigated disturbances were placed under administrative detention in accordance with the law.

Beijing announces 3 cases of imported confirmed cases

On July 17, Beijing reported 3 CONFIRMED CASES IMPORTED FROM ABROAD:

Huang Mou, female, 22 years old, registered permanent residence in Chengdu, Sichuan Province, studying in London, UK. March 6 headache, sore throat and other symptoms, 10 to the clinic, according to the doctor to buy throat spray, 14 dry cough. On the 15th, Russia by Russian Airlines SU262 from London to Moscow, by Russian Airlines SU204 from Moscow back to Beijing, the plane filled in the health declaration card, sore throat and other symptoms. After arriving in Beijing at 10:00 on the 16th, he was transferred to a designated hospital for screening and was diagnosed as a confirmed case on the 17th.

Du Mou, Male, 41 years old, registered permanent residence in Xicheng District, Beijing. March 1-14 from Beijing to Madrid, Spain, Sao Paulo, Brazil. During his stay in Madrid, he went shopping in a supermarket without a mask. Arrived in Beijing in the early morning of the 14th, because was identified as high-risk personnel, for centralized isolation medical observation. Fever and other symptoms, body temperature 39.2 °C, transferred to the designated hospital screening, 17 diagnosed as a confirmed case.

Xie Mou, female, 27 years old, registered permanent residence in Nanchong, Sichuan Province, studying in Manchester, UK. On March 2, she had fever, self-reported temperature of 36.2 °C, did not see a doctor, and had nasal congestion on the 5th. Singapore Airlines SQ051 by the 15th from the United Kingdom to Singapore, 16 by Singapore Airlines SQ802 to Beijing. Xu arrived in Beijing at 15:00 on the 16th and reported sore throat at the customs. He was transferred to a designated hospital for screening and was diagnosed as a confirmed case on the 17th.

Mass immunization isn't working. Vaccines are the key

What lessons can China learn from other countries? In response, Zhong Nanshan said: one is a strong intervention method, the other is China's proposed joint prevention and control, prevention from the source.

We can't rely on "collective immunity" to solve the problem, says Zhong Nanshan, because NCP is a disease with a high mortality rate. There is no evidence that once you get sick, you're immune forever. At this point, the most important task is to produce an effective vaccine as soon as possible, the next step will require closer international cooperation.

The development of a new Chinese crown vaccine will not be much worse than that of the United States

So far, the development of Vaccine Research and development is also a point of great concern. Zhong Nanshan said that at present, the research and development of China's new coronavirus vaccine is mainly in five directions: First, the whole virus vaccine, such as the H1N1 vaccine in 2009; second, the nucleic acid vaccine; third, the vaccine with Adenovirus as a vector; fourth, the protein vaccine with genetic engineering; Fifth, the influenza as a vector vaccine.

All five vaccines are developing very fast in China, not much worse than in the United States.

More News:

Zhong Nanshan: New Crown Pneumonia outbreak in Wuhan, does not mean the source in Wuhan

Zhong Nanshan said on the 18th that the new pneumonia outbreak occurred in Wuhan, China, but did not mean that the source in Wuhan, he pointed out that this is a scientific problem. It's irresponsible to jump to conclusions without knowing what's going on.

84-year-old health lesson from Zhong Nanshan: Don't overeat

At the press conference, Zhong Nanshan, 84, also shared his own health experiences. He said the first is to strengthen exercise, no job can take the place of it. The second is mentality, half of health is mental health, the third is not to eat too much. "This is very important. I never eat too much. Breakfast is very important. "
